headline: Republican state attorneys pressure Costco to drop diversity policies
summary: Nineteen Republican attorneys general have called on Costco Wholesale to abandon its diversity, equity, and inclusion policies, citing concerns about discrimination and legal risks. This comes after 98% of the U.S. retailer's shareholders last week voted against a proposal requesting a report on the risks tied to its diversity and inclusion initiatives, pushing back against the growing scrutiny such policies face. Costco did not immediately respond to a Reuters request for comment outside regular business hours.
